transcript.transcript:
Agent: Hello, thank you for calling Pennie. My name is John Smith, how can I help you today?
Customer: Hi, I am looking for health insurance.
Agent: I would be happy to help you with that. Can I get your full name please?
Customer: Sure, my name is Jane Doe.
Agent: Thank you Jane. And can I get your date of birth?
Customer: January 15, 1960.
Agent: Great. Let me pull up some plans for you. Based on your information, I have a few options. The first plan is a Silver plan at $150 per month with a $2000 deductible.
Customer: That sounds good. What about dental?
Agent: Dental is included in this plan. Let me go over the details with you. The plan covers preventive care at 100%, and major services at 50%.
Customer: Ok, I would like to enroll in that plan.
Agent: Wonderful! Let me get you enrolled. I will need to verify a few things. Can you confirm your address?
Customer: 123 Main Street, Philadelphia PA 19101.
Agent: Perfect. And your monthly household income?
Customer: About $3,500 per month.
Agent: Thank you. Based on your income, you qualify for a subsidy that brings your premium down to $50 per month.
Customer: That is great!
Agent: Excellent. I have submitted your application. You should receive a confirmation within 24 hours. Is there anything else I can help you with?
Customer: No, that is all. Thank you so much for your help.
Agent: You are welcome Jane. Thank you for choosing Pennie and have a great day!

ideal_script: Standard enrollment script for Medicare AEP campaign.
